The paper focuses on advancing state-of-the-art in text detection and recognition in natural images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for text classification, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper identifies significant shortcomings in current approaches, which suggests the need for further research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
